FOODBORNE ILLNESS - EGYPT: (SUEZ) SCHOOLCHILDREN, MILK SUSPECTED, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*****************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 22 Oct 2014
Source: AllAfrica, Aswat Masriya report [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201410230249.html


Egypt's top prosecutor ordered on [Wed 22 Oct 2014] a swift investigation into the 178 cases of food poisoning reported in 2 primary schools in Suez.

Ayman Samir, the ministry of education's media official in Suez, told Aswat Masriya that the poisoning was caused by the consumption of milk provided by the schools. He added that the ministry's deputy to Suez, Abdel Hafez Waheed, halted the distribution of milk to all schools in the governorate until the milk's validity is ensured.

At least 3 outbreaks of food poisoning occurred at al-Azhar University between April and May 2013. Over 700 cases of food poisoning were detected in the university's male dorms.

