communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It is necessary to know the incubation period related to the milk ingestion and the symptom complex related to fever, vomiting, and or diarrhea to assess the potential etiology of the illnesses. Many infections can be associated with unpasteurized milk as seen in the "See Also" list below. Pasteurized milk can also transmit infections if the pasteurization is not adequate or contamination occurs after the process. Illnesses can also be related to toxins rather than infection.

Suez (http://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suez) is a seaport city in north eastern Egypt, located on the north coast of the Gulf of Suez (a branch of the Red Sea), near the southern terminus of the Suez Canal, having the same boundaries as Suez governorate. - Mod.LL

Maps of Egypt can be seen at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Governorates_of_Egypt and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2894125,11622. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
